['Merantix Labs - Business Development & Project Management

Full-time position - Berlin, Germany

What we Do

Merantix is a pioneering technology lab and incubation platform for Artificial Intelligence. Our mission is to conceptualize, build and scale AI products that transform entire industries and organizations. Merantix incubation platform is distinct in its access to world-class engineering and business talent, its trusted brand among corporations and regulators as well as its sophisticated technology stack, all of which accelerate prototyping and productization. It has currently built three companies: MX Healthcare, MX Automotive and MX Labs.

MX Labs conceptualizes, builds, and scales machine-learning solutions for clients across all industries. Our current projects include developing logistics solutions for retailers, quality assurance tools for manufacturing, machine-learning systems for financials providers and a cancer detection system for a healthcare provider. We take advantage of three core competencies: our experience applying machine learning, our expertise fostering enterprise partnerships to assemble vast datasets, and our culture of rapid iterations to build scalable products.

Our team is made up of entrepreneurs, scientists, and engineers from premier universities around the world. Many of us have PhDs and work experience at top tech companies. We’re based in Europe’s startup capital, Berlin, and are growing quickly!

Your Role

On our path to becoming Europe’s #1 breeding ground for AI products, we seek entrepreneurial minds that have the ambition to disrupt markets with the latest AI technology. In order to build outstanding client-focused solutions with the help of a distinguished team, state-of-the-art machine learning technology as well as a clear focus on creating real-world impact, we are looking for talented business development. If that resonates with you, here is what your role at Merantix Labs includes:

Proactively drive and fully own client acquisition from outreach to closing;

Scope, structure and design machine learning solutions and manage projects with clients from different industries;

Ideate, conceptualize and facilitate workshops for clients (including C-level);

Represent Merantix at conference, events and talk;

Develop a deep understanding of our business and industry, and proactively identify; strategic or operational opportunities to drive additional value for the company;

Take ownership of your subprojects from the idea generation and requirement gathering to the successful implementation of our clients and partners solutions;

Work with different teams across Merantix to ensure execution and successful delivery of end to end projects;

Develop strategic initiatives from conceptualization to implementation of strategic initiatives; proactively improve processes for you and the team.

Your Qualifications

We define ourselves by a culture of ownership and cooperation. We are looking for driven, capable, visionary and prudent talents with proven track records of personal, academic and professional achievement:

MA/MSc/MBA in business engineering, computer science or engineering from a top-tier university;

2+years professional experience preferably at a leading technology company, management consultancy, investment bank or similar environment;

Long-held interest in technology, both personally & professionally;

Excellent technical and analytical problem-solving skills, with the ability to step back and contextualize the problem and its root;

Strong organizational and multitasking skills with the ability to prioritize appropriately and effectively, investigative problem at hand, deep dive to the root cause of a problem and support it with analytical data;

Fluent written and oral German and English;

Entrepreneurial mindset: Creative, focused, and highly motivated;

Excellent communication (verbal and written) and interpersonal skills to effectively communicate with biz and tech teams;

Love what you do (and own it).

Preferable qualifications:

PhD is a plus;

Technical knowledge in machine learning;

A professional network in the EU tech ecosystem is a plus;

Industry domain knowledge is a plus;

Additional languages are a plus.

Working at Merantix

Our hierarchy is flat and communication direct, which means that we operate and learn fast, as a team. You are a great fit for our team if this describes you:

Entrepreneurial mindset: creative, focused, and not easily discouraged;

An ability to work in a fast-paced, highly innovative environment where ambiguity is the norm;

Excellent technical and analytical problem-solving skills, with the ability to step back and contextualize the problem and its root;

Independent but cooperative mindset;

Strong organizational and multitasking skills with ability to prioritize appropriately and effectively;

Love what you do (and own it).

In addition to a competitive salary you can expect the following:

Engaging topics:

Merantix offers unique insights in applied machine learning research and development, working with a group of highly talented engineers and entrepreneurs. Joining a dynamic, young company with an interdisciplinary team, you are encouraged to pursue your curiosity for a variety of topics and to approach challenges in creative and innovative ways.

Dynamic working culture:

Merantix offers a dynamic and flexible work environment. We are a fully trust-based organization and believe in ownership of work, personal responsibility, and the motivation of our people.

Excellence:

We are driven researchers, developers and entrepreneurs who believe in what they create and are committed to the success of their ventures. In order to build disruptive products, we strive for outstanding quality and visionary ideas in a high-performance environment.

We are an equal-opportunity employer and value diversity. We consider all applications equally regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, or gender identity. We strongly encourage individuals from groups traditionally underrepresented in tech to apply, and we can help with immigration.']

